The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Feb. 2: Home loan financier HDFC today announced a special monthly deposit product for its customers that promises higher returns by offering variable interest rates. The product, which is similar to the recurring deposit (RD) scheme offered by banks, promises variable interest rate earnings unlike the fixed interest rate structure of RDs.                            
	 New Delhi, Feb. 2: The Centre has extended till September the stock limit order for sugar, under which the states are empowered to take action against hoarders and black marketeers. The validity of the anti-hoarding order, first issued last March, was to expire on January 3. The order was earlier extended for six months last July.                             
	 Calcutta, Feb. 2: Emami has inducted Priti Sureka, daughter of promoter R.S. Agarwal on its board with three other independent directors. The company has also posted a 30.3 per cent rise in its consolidated turnover at Rs 350 crore (including inorganic growth of 6.5 per cent) for the quarter.                             
	 New Delhi, Feb. 2: The issue of equity infusion into Air India and a review of its turnaround plans are expected to come up for a discussion by a group of ministers headed by finance minister Pranab Mukherjee tomorrow.                            
	 New Delhi, Feb. 2: The government will divest up to 15 per cent stake in state-run Coal India Ltd in the next six months. The government, at present, holds a 100 per cent stake in the countrys largest coal producer.                             
	 New Delhi, Feb. 2: The countrys mutual fund industry witnessed a decline in the average assets under management for the second month in a row to Rs 7.61 lakh crore in January.                            
	 Calcutta, Feb. 2: Balmer Lawrie has posted a rise in total income to Rs 410 crore in the quarter ended 31 December 2009 from Rs 409 crore in the year-ago period.
                                                                                                                          
